'''Debbie Gross''' is the founder and director of the religious women crisis center Tahel.<ref name="The Jerusalem Post">{{cite web|last1=Levi|first1=Sarah|title=Sexual abuse in the Ultra-Orthodox world|url=https://www.pressreader.com/israel/jerusalem-post/20171128/281612420715893|publisher=The Jerusalem Post|accessdate=8 April 2018}}</ref> She founded the organization in 1993<ref name="The Media Line">{{cite web|last1=Abumaria|first1=Dima|title=Tackling the Sexual Abuse Taboo among Religious Jews|url=http://www.themedialine.org/top-stories/tackling-sexual-abuse-taboo-among-religious-jews/|publisher=The Media Line|accessdate=8 April 2018}}</ref> to help women in a time of crisis and now it is a national center in [[Israel]] to help women and children dealing with trauma.<ref name="Arutz Sheva">{{cite web|last1=Poch|first1=Raphael|title=Putting sexual violence and abuse center stage|url=https://www.israelnationalnews.com/News/News.aspx/204332|publisher=Arutz Sheva|accessdate=8 April 2018}}</ref> She is a [[psychologist]] and [[social worker]] by trade and a previous winner of a number of awards. These include the Jerusalem Mayor's Volunteer Award from Prime Minister [[Ehud Olmert]] in 2001, the [[Jerusalem Foundation]] Teddy Kollek Award for Community Leadership and Excellence in 2003, the [[Knesset]] award for “Women Who Are Changing The World” in 2016, and “The Award for Recognition for Fighting the Battle Against Violence Against Women” by the Minister of Social Equality of Israel in 2017.<ref name="The Bright Beginnings">{{cite web|title=Debbie Gross|url=https://thebrightbeginnings.com/author/debbie-gross/|publisher=The Bright Beginnings|accessdate=8 April 2018}}</ref>  In December of 2017, Tahel announced a set of “Ten Guidelines” which are ethics guidelines for religious leaders to advocate for proper conduct with their congregants. The guidelines are [[interfaith]] and have been signed by religious leaders of many faiths. <ref name="Forward">{{cite web|title=Interfaith Organization Issues Guidelines for Religious Leaders to Pevent Sexual Offenses|url=https://forward.com/fast-forward/388907/interfaith-organization-issues-guidelines-for-religious-leaders-to-prevent/|publisher=Forward|accessdate=8 April 2018}}</ref> 

